People always ask me what do I do about depression, anxiety, and overthinking. We all struggle with these. 2020 was one of my worse years, I fell into depression and didn’t wanna do anything besides work and sleep. Then I realized it was up to me ONLY to make a change and decide how I wanted to live the rest of my life. One thing I knew; I had to constantly keep moving. In 2021 I started my 5am mornings (having my first wrestling class at 5:30) and cold showers around 7:30am everyday.  This routine changed my way of living completely. So when people ask me what’s my answer to depression, this is it. Wake up everyday being grateful for your life, exercise is a MUST, drink a LOT of water, text good morning to the people you care about! let it go of people who doesn’t add anything in your life, get used to being ALONE, always demand RESPECT and remember to stay quiet about your plans and life overall. They wanna see you do good, but never better than them.
